## Quick Start

### 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env and add your API keys
```

{{#if includeLLM}}
**Required API keys:**
{{#if hasAnthropic}}
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` - Get from https://console.anthropic.com/
{{/if}}
{{#if hasOpenAI}}
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` - Get from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
{{/if}}
{{#if hasGemini}}
- `GOOGLE_API_KEY` - Get from https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
{{/if}}

{{/if}}
### 3. Start Development Server

```bash
# STDIO mode (recommended for MCP Inspector)
npm run dev:stdio

# HTTP mode (skip auth - dev only)
npm run dev:http

{{#if includeAuth}}
# HTTP mode with OAuth (production-like)
npm run dev:oauth
{{/if}}
```

### 4. Test with MCP Inspector

```bash
# In a separate terminal
npm install -g @modelcontextprotocol/inspector
mcp-inspector
```

Then connect to `http://localhost:3000` (or use STDIO mode).

## Available Tools

### Basic Tools

- **hello** - Greet users by name
  ```json
  {
    "name": "hello",
    "arguments": { "name": "World" }
  }
  ```

- **echo** - Echo back messages
  ```json
  {
    "name": "echo",
    "arguments": { "message": "Hello!" }
  }
  ```

- **current-time** - Get current timestamp
  ```json
  {
    "name": "current-time",
    "arguments": {}
  }
  ```

{{#if includeLLM}}
### LLM-Powered Tools

- **chat** - Interactive AI assistant
- **analyze** - Deep text analysis
- **summarize** - Text summarization
- **explain** - Educational explanations

{{/if}}
## Development

### Available Scripts

```bash
npm run dev:stdio        # STDIO mode
npm run dev:http         # HTTP mode (no auth)
{{#if includeAuth}}
npm run dev:oauth        # HTTP mode with OAuth
{{/if}}
npm run build            # Build project
npm test                 # Run tests
npm run validate         # Full validation (required before commit)
npm run typecheck        # TypeScript type checking
npm run lint             # Code linting
```

### Adding New Tools

1. Create tool file: `src/tools/my-tool.ts`
2. Register tool: Add to `src/tools/index.ts`
3. Add test: `test/tools/my-tool.test.ts`
4. Run validation: `npm run validate`

See `CLAUDE.md` for detailed guidance on adding tools.

